<https://w3id.org/tc/capsule/dev.enforce_todo_ticket_v1> a tc:Capsule ;
    dct:created "2025-11-10T00:00:00+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dct:creator "Truth Capsules" ;
    dct:identifier "dev.enforce_todo_ticket_v1" ;
    dct:license "MIT" ;
    dct:modified "2025-11-10T00:00:00+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dct:title "Enforce TODO/FIXME Lines Reference a Ticket" ;
    ns1:affiliation "Truth Capsules Demo" ;
    ns1:version "1.0.0" ;
    tc:applies_to "ci",
        "code_assistant" ;
    tc:assumption "Diff is a standard unified diff (e.g., `git diff`).",
        "Reviewers accept TODOs only when linked to tracked work.",
        "Ticket prefix is stable and communicated to the team." ;
    tc:domain "dev" ;
    tc:hasWitness <https://w3id.org/tc/capsule/dev.enforce_todo_ticket_v1#w/todo_refs_present> ;
    tc:inBundle <https://w3id.org/tc/bundle/bundle.dev_code_assistant_v1> ;
    tc:sensitivity "low" ;
    tc:statement """Any newly added TODO/FIXME lines in a diff must include a valid ticket reference.
Default format is `(PROJ|JIRA)-[0-9]+` and can be customized with env `TICKET_REGEX`.
Scope: added lines only (unified diff), excluding headers (`+++`, `@@`, `diff --git`).
Pass criteria:
  • If no TODO/FIXME were added ⇒ PASS.
  • If TODO/FIXME were added ⇒ each TODO line must contain a ticket reference that matches `TICKET_REGEX`.""" .

<https://w3id.org/tc/capsule/dev.prompt_safety_rules_v1> a tc:Capsule ;
    dct:created "2025-11-10T20:25:00+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dct:creator "John Macgregor" ;
    dct:identifier "dev.prompt_safety_rules_v1" ;
    dct:license "MIT" ;
    dct:modified "2025-11-10T20:25:00+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    dct:title "Prompt Safety Rules (No Secrets, No PHI/PII, Scratchpad Discipline)" ;
    ns1:affiliation "Truth Capsules Demo" ;
    ns1:version "1.0.0" ;
    tc:applies_to "code_assistant",
        "conversation",
        "review" ;
    tc:domain "dev" ;
    tc:inBundle <https://w3id.org/tc/bundle/bundle.dev_code_assistant_v1> ;
    tc:reviewStatus "draft" ;
    tc:sensitivity "medium" ;
    tc:statement """Guardrails for safe, reproducible dev prompting.

Do
  • Redact or mask secrets/PHI/PII before pasting (tokens, keys, emails, phone numbers).
  • Use a scratchpad file; summarize context; paste only minimal diffs, errors, and file paths.
  • State desired output explicitly (patch/diff, function signature, CLI snippet).
  • Declare toolchain versions and OS when relevant (python 3.11, node 20, ubuntu 22.04).
  • Prefer small, testable changes; include tests or commands to verify.

Don’t
  • Paste .env, private keys, customer data, or production URLs.
  • Demand sweeping refactors; avoid touching unrelated files.
  • Bury the lede — put the objective first; attach diagnostics after.

Scratchpad discipline
  • Keep a running PLAN → VERIFY → ANSWER section.
  • Use fenced code blocks for diffs/patches; keep commit-ready.""" .

